      • associateTokenAndReceiver

        public void associateTokenAndReceiver​(java.lang.String token,
                                      JsonReceiver jsonReceiver)
        Adds a token to a token registry. If the token has already sent, is not added, because it's already there. This happens when a client disconnects and reconnects. Then, creates an association between the token and the jsonReceiver of the client. If a token is already associated with a json receiver, this method fails.
        Parameters:
        token - token of the client
        jsonReceiver - jsonReceiver of the client

      • associateReceiverAndUser

        associates the given json receiver and user. A json receiver can exist while the user is still null
        Parameters:
        jr - client json receiver
        user - user that is associated to this
